Sentencas: This work investigates the effect of contact between electrodes and alloy interconnects on output performance of solid oxide fuel cell (.SOFC) stacks.
Titulo: Effect of Contact between Electrode and Interconnect on Performance of SOFC Stacks

Sentencas: The measured maximum output power density (p(max)) of the unit cell increases from 0.07 to 0.1 W cm(-2) by increasing the tip area of the interconnect from 40 to 60 cm(2).
Titulo: Effect of Contact between Electrode and Interconnect on Performance of SOFC Stacks

Sentencas: The pmax increases from 0.07 to 0.15 W cm(-2) upon the addition of nickel foam and Ag mesh on the anode and cathode side, respectively.
Titulo: Effect of Contact between Electrode and Interconnect on Performance of SOFC Stacks

Sentencas: An additional (La0.75Sr0.25)(0.95)MO3-sigma cathode current collecting layer is reprinted on the original cathode current collecting layer, which aims to further improve the performance of the stack and individual cell.
Titulo: Effect of Contact between Electrode and Interconnect on Performance of SOFC Stacks

Sentencas: The performance of a 3-cell short stack assembled by the cells with a new cathode current collecting layer is evaluated by measuring the current-voltage curve.
Titulo: Effect of Contact between Electrode and Interconnect on Performance of SOFC Stacks

Sentencas: The results indicate that the pmax values of the stack and individual cells are enhanced from 0.07 to 0.37 W cm(-2) and 0.15 to 0.5 W cm(-2) at 850 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Effect of Contact between Electrode and Interconnect on Performance of SOFC Stacks

Sentencas: The performance of the whole stack and individual cells is greatly improved due to the interconnect embedded in the re-printed new cathode current collecting layer.
Titulo: Effect of Contact between Electrode and Interconnect on Performance of SOFC Stacks
